trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <see cref="T:System.Windows.Media.PathFigure" /> objects that collectively make up the geometry of a <see cref="T:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry" />.
trans-unit.target: Rappresenta una raccolta di oggetti <see cref="T:System.Windows.Media.PathFigure" /> che collettivamente costituiscono la geometria di <see cref="T:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry" />.

trans-unit.source: Except as noted, members of this class behave exactly as described by the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IList%601>, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.ICollection%601>, and <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601> documentation.
trans-unit.target: Se non specificato, i membri di questa classe si comportano esattamente come descritto nella <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IList%601>, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.ICollection%601>, e <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable%601> documentazione.

trans-unit.source: **Freezable Features:** Because it inherits from the <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> class, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigureCollection> class provides several special features: <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigureCollection> objects can be declared as , shared among multiple objects, made read-only to improve performance, cloned, and made thread-safe.
trans-unit.target: **Funzionalità dell'oggetto Freezable:** perché eredita dal <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> (classe), il <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigureCollection> classe fornisce diverse funzionalità speciali: <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathFigureCollection> oggetti possono essere dichiarati come, condivisi tra più oggetti, in sola lettura per migliorare prestazioni, duplicati e resi thread-safe.

trans-unit.source: For more information about the different features provided by <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> objects, see the [Freezable Objects Overview](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/freezable-objects-overview.md).
trans-unit.target: Per ulteriori informazioni sulle diverse funzionalità fornite da <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> degli oggetti, vedere il [panoramica sugli oggetti Freezable](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/freezable-objects-overview.md).
